          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @Jonty- I didn't expect anything different, cold or not. Stoke can only score against the top teams 2 ways- long ball to a target man to either get a chance themselves or knock it down to an arriving player or on the counter- which is true of every team in the prem if you defend too high and attack with the wing backs 3 quarters of the way down the pitch. Chelsea, since the early part of the season when Leicester, Swansea and Burnely were able to fashion chances against them which were most un-Chelsea-like have kept it solid at the back- compact and defending at the right distance when attacking, like it was in Mourinho's first spell, so the counter attack is for the most part taken away and have 2 centre backs, and to be fair also 2 full backs, who don't mind contesting such balls. Their 3rd option was let Bojan try and work his magic which is impossible when the supporting cast is mediocre.

          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            @khonda- That's cos he's a dying breed. Everyone needs a clean-up midfielder who can pass to the more gifted passers but it seems the 1 position that has a severe lack of numbers. I expect within the next few seasons, at least 10 players of his type to be floating around the big teams of Europe. It's definitely a player us (Arsenal), Man Utd and Man City could all do with although with Fernandinho playing, City are ok in that department. Matic on his own, and players of his type, wont make a difference to a team that doesn't already contain gifted playmakers because that's not his forte, but adding him to a midfield which has a gifted passer, gifted dribbler and gifted mover allows the latter 3 to do their thing without worrying what's going on behind em. It's an invaluable part of the midfield jigsaw puzzle. Matic isn't the only 1 but he's the best of those that there are.
